article.headline: South Florida 73, Murray St. 64
article.story: GUAYNABO, Puerto Rico -- Dominique Jones scored 23 points to lead South Florida to a 73-64 win against Murray State on Saturday. Jones was 5-for-7 from beyond the arc for the Bulls (4-5), who won for the first time since beating Northeastern 55-37 in late November this year. The Bulls hit 6 of 17 3-pointers compared to a 2-for-13 mark for the Racers (5-4) in the opening game for both teams in the San Juan Shootout. University of Georgia transfer Mike Mercer scored 12 points in his third game for South Florida. Danero Thomas led the Racers with 16 points and Tyler Holloway added 11. The Bulls, who led 35-28 at halftime, outrebounded the Racers 36-29 en route to victory. South Florida will play Wright State on Sunday in the tournament, while Murray State will play Oral Roberts.
